61static void
62puts_param_types(FILE * fp, param *list, int more)
63{
64 param *p;
65
66 if (list != 0)
67 {
68 for (p = list; p; p = p->next)
69 {
70 size_t len_type = strlen(p->type);
71 fprintf(fp, "%s%s%s%s%s", p->type,
72 (((len_type != 0) && (p->type[len_type - 1] == '*'))
73 ? ""
74 : " "),
75 p->name, p->type2,
76 ((more || p->next) ? ", " : ""));
77 }
78 }
79 else
80 {
81 if (!more)
82 fprintf(fp, "void");
83 }
84}

118static void
119define_prefixed(FILE * fp, const char *name)
120{
121 int bump_line = CountLine(fp);
122 if (bump_line)
123 ++outline;
124 fprintf(fp, "\n");
125
126 if (bump_line)
127 ++outline;
128 fprintf(fp, "#ifndef %s\n", name);
129
130 if (bump_line)
131 ++outline;
132 fprintf(fp, "#define %-10s %s%s\n", name, symbol_prefix, name + 2);
133
134 if (bump_line)
135 ++outline;
136 fprintf(fp, "#endif /* %s */\n", name);
137}

288static void
289output_rule_data(void)
290{
291 int i;
292 int j;
293
294 output_YYINT_typedef(output_file);
295
296 start_int_table("lhs", symbol_value[start_symbol]);
297
298 j = 10;
299 for (i = 3; i < nrules; i++)
300 {
301 if (j >= 10)
302 {
303 output_newline();
304 j = 1;
305 }
306 else
307 ++j;
308
309 output_int(symbol_value[rlhs[i]]);
310 }
311 end_table();
312
313 start_int_table("len", 2);
314
315 j = 10;
316 for (i = 3; i < nrules; i++)
317 {
318 if (j >= 10)
319 {
320 output_newline();
321 j = 1;
322 }
323 else
324 j++;
325
326 output_int(rrhs[i + 1] - rrhs[i] - 1);
327 }
328 end_table();
329}

400static Value_t
401find_conflict_base(int cbase)
402{
403 int i, j;
404
405 for (i = 0; i < cbase; i++)
406 {
407 for (j = 0; j + cbase < nconflicts; j++)
408 {
409 if (conflicts[i + j] != conflicts[cbase + j])
410 break;
411 }
412 if (j + cbase >= nconflicts)
413 break;
414 }
415 return (Value_t)i;
416}
417#endif
418
419static void
420token_actions(void)
421{
422 int i, j;
423 Value_t shiftcount, reducecount;
424#if defined(YYBTYACC)
425 Value_t conflictcount = 0;
426 Value_t csym = -1;
427 Value_t cbase = 0;
428#endif
429 int max, min;
430 Value_t *actionrow, *r, *s;
431 action *p;
432
433 actionrow = NEW2(PER_STATE * ntokens, Value_t);
434 for (i = 0; i < nstates; ++i)
435 {
436 if (parser[i])
437 {
438 for (j = 0; j < PER_STATE * ntokens; ++j)
439 actionrow[j] = 0;
440
441 shiftcount = 0;
442 reducecount = 0;
443#if defined(YYBTYACC)
444 if (backtrack)
445 {
446 conflictcount = 0;
447 csym = -1;
448 cbase = nconflicts;
449 }
450#endif
451 for (p = parser[i]; p; p = p->next)
452 {
453#if defined(YYBTYACC)
454 if (backtrack)
455 {
456 if (csym != -1 && csym != p->symbol)
457 {
458 conflictcount++;
459 conflicts[nconflicts++] = -1;
460 j = find_conflict_base(cbase);
461 actionrow[csym + 2 * ntokens] = (Value_t)(j + 1);
462 if (j == cbase)
463 {
464 cbase = nconflicts;
465 }
466 else
467 {
468 if (conflicts[cbase] == -1)
469 cbase++;
470 nconflicts = cbase;
471 }
472 csym = -1;
473 }
474 }
475#endif
476 if (p->suppressed == 0)
477 {
478 if (p->action_code == SHIFT)
479 {
480 ++shiftcount;
481 actionrow[p->symbol] = p->number;
482 }
483 else if (p->action_code == REDUCE && p->number != defred[i])
484 {
485 ++reducecount;
486 actionrow[p->symbol + ntokens] = p->number;
487 }
488 }
489#if defined(YYBTYACC)
490 else if (backtrack && p->suppressed == 1)
491 {
492 csym = p->symbol;
493 if (p->action_code == SHIFT)
494 {
495 conflicts[nconflicts++] = p->number;
496 }
497 else if (p->action_code == REDUCE && p->number != defred[i])
498 {
499 if (cbase == nconflicts)
500 {
501 if (cbase)
502 cbase--;
503 else
504 conflicts[nconflicts++] = -1;
505 }
506 conflicts[nconflicts++] = (Value_t)(p->number - 2);
507 }
508 }
509#endif
510 }
511#if defined(YYBTYACC)
512 if (backtrack && csym != -1)
513 {
514 conflictcount++;
515 conflicts[nconflicts++] = -1;
516 j = find_conflict_base(cbase);
517 actionrow[csym + 2 * ntokens] = (Value_t)(j + 1);
518 if (j == cbase)
519 {
520 cbase = nconflicts;
521 }
522 else
523 {
524 if (conflicts[cbase] == -1)
525 cbase++;
526 nconflicts = cbase;
527 }
528 }
529#endif
530
531 tally[i] = shiftcount;
532 tally[nstates + i] = reducecount;
533#if defined(YYBTYACC)
534 if (backtrack)
535 tally[2 * nstates + i] = conflictcount;
536#endif
537 width[i] = 0;
538 width[nstates + i] = 0;
539#if defined(YYBTYACC)
540 if (backtrack)
541 width[2 * nstates + i] = 0;
542#endif
543 if (shiftcount > 0)
544 {
545 froms[i] = r = NEW2(shiftcount, Value_t);
546 tos[i] = s = NEW2(shiftcount, Value_t);
547 min = MAXYYINT;
548 max = 0;
549 for (j = 0; j < ntokens; ++j)
550 {
551 if (actionrow[j])
552 {
553 if (min > symbol_value[j])
554 min = symbol_value[j];
555 if (max < symbol_value[j])
556 max = symbol_value[j];
557 *r++ = symbol_value[j];
558 *s++ = actionrow[j];
559 }
560 }
561 width[i] = (Value_t)(max - min + 1);
562 }
563 if (reducecount > 0)
564 {
565 froms[nstates + i] = r = NEW2(reducecount, Value_t);
566 tos[nstates + i] = s = NEW2(reducecount, Value_t);
567 min = MAXYYINT;
568 max = 0;
569 for (j = 0; j < ntokens; ++j)
570 {
571 if (actionrow[ntokens + j])
572 {
573 if (min > symbol_value[j])
574 min = symbol_value[j];
575 if (max < symbol_value[j])
576 max = symbol_value[j];
577 *r++ = symbol_value[j];
578 *s++ = (Value_t)(actionrow[ntokens + j] - 2);
579 }
580 }
581 width[nstates + i] = (Value_t)(max - min + 1);
582 }
583#if defined(YYBTYACC)
584 if (backtrack && conflictcount > 0)
585 {
586 froms[2 * nstates + i] = r = NEW2(conflictcount, Value_t);
587 tos[2 * nstates + i] = s = NEW2(conflictcount, Value_t);
588 min = MAXYYINT;
589 max = 0;
590 for (j = 0; j < ntokens; ++j)
591 {
592 if (actionrow[2 * ntokens + j])
593 {
594 if (min > symbol_value[j])
595 min = symbol_value[j];
596 if (max < symbol_value[j])
597 max = symbol_value[j];
598 *r++ = symbol_value[j];
599 *s++ = (Value_t)(actionrow[2 * ntokens + j] - 1);
600 }
601 }
602 width[2 * nstates + i] = (Value_t)(max - min + 1);
603 }
604#endif
605 }
606 }
607 FREE(actionrow);
608}

610static int
611default_goto(int symbol)
612{
613 int i;
614 int m;
615 int n;
616 int default_state;
617 int max;
618
619 m = goto_map[symbol];
620 n = goto_map[symbol + 1];
621
622 if (m == n)
623 return (0);
624
625 for (i = 0; i < nstates; i++)
626 state_count[i] = 0;
627
628 for (i = m; i < n; i++)
629 state_count[to_state[i]]++;
630
631 max = 0;
632 default_state = 0;
633 for (i = 0; i < nstates; i++)
634 {
635 if (state_count[i] > max)
636 {
637 max = state_count[i];
638 default_state = i;
639 }
640 }
641
642 return (default_state);
643}

645static void
646save_column(int symbol, int default_state)
647{
648 int i;
649 int m;
650 int n;
651 Value_t *sp;
652 Value_t *sp1;
653 Value_t *sp2;
654 Value_t count;
655 int symno;
656
657 m = goto_map[symbol];
658 n = goto_map[symbol + 1];
659
660 count = 0;
661 for (i = m; i < n; i++)
662 {
663 if (to_state[i] != default_state)
664 ++count;
665 }
666 if (count == 0)
667 return;
668
669 symno = symbol_value[symbol] + PER_STATE * nstates;
670
671 froms[symno] = sp1 = sp = NEW2(count, Value_t);
672 tos[symno] = sp2 = NEW2(count, Value_t);
673
674 for (i = m; i < n; i++)
675 {
676 if (to_state[i] != default_state)
677 {
678 *sp1++ = from_state[i];
679 *sp2++ = to_state[i];
680 }
681 }
682
683 tally[symno] = count;
684 width[symno] = (Value_t)(sp1[-1] - sp[0] + 1);
685}

687static void
688goto_actions(void)
689{
690 int i, j, k;
691
692 state_count = NEW2(nstates, Value_t);
693
694 k = default_goto(start_symbol + 1);
695 start_int_table("dgoto", k);
696 save_column(start_symbol + 1, k);
697
698 j = 10;
699 for (i = start_symbol + 2; i < nsyms; i++)
700 {
701 if (j >= 10)
702 {
703 output_newline();
704 j = 1;
705 }
706 else
707 ++j;
708
709 k = default_goto(i);
710 output_int(k);
711 save_column(i, k);
712 }
713
714 end_table();
715 FREE(state_count);
716}

718static void
719sort_actions(void)
720{
721 Value_t i;
722 int j;
723 int k;
724 int t;
725 int w;
726
727 order = NEW2(nvectors, Value_t);
728 nentries = 0;
729
730 for (i = 0; i < nvectors; i++)
731 {
732 if (tally[i] > 0)
733 {
734 t = tally[i];
735 w = width[i];
736 j = nentries - 1;
737
738 while (j >= 0 && (width[order[j]] < w))
739 j--;
740
741 while (j >= 0 && (width[order[j]] == w) && (tally[order[j]] < t))
742 j--;
743
744 for (k = nentries - 1; k > j; k--)
745 order[k + 1] = order[k];
746
747 order[j + 1] = i;
748 nentries++;
749 }
750 }
751}

753/* The function matching_vector determines if the vector specified by */
754/* the input parameter matches a previously considered vector. The */
755/* test at the start of the function checks if the vector represents */
756/* a row of shifts over terminal symbols or a row of reductions, or a */
757/* column of shifts over a nonterminal symbol. Berkeley Yacc does not */
758/* check if a column of shifts over a nonterminal symbols matches a */
759/* previously considered vector. Because of the nature of LR parsing */
760/* tables, no two columns can match. Therefore, the only possible */
761/* match would be between a row and a column. Such matches are */
762/* unlikely. Therefore, to save time, no attempt is made to see if a */
763/* column matches a previously considered vector. */
764/* */
765/* Matching_vector is poorly designed. The test could easily be made */
766/* faster. Also, it depends on the vectors being in a specific */
767/* order. */
768#if defined(YYBTYACC)
769/* */
770/* Not really any point in checking for matching conflicts -- it is */
771/* extremely unlikely to occur, and conflicts are (hopefully) rare. */
772#endif
773
774static int
775matching_vector(int vector)
776{
777 int i;
778 int j;
779 int k;
780 int t;
781 int w;
782 int match;
783 int prev;
784
785 i = order[vector];
786 if (i >= 2 * nstates)
787 return (-1);
788
789 t = tally[i];
790 w = width[i];
791
792 for (prev = vector - 1; prev >= 0; prev--)
793 {
794 j = order[prev];
795 if (width[j] != w || tally[j] != t)
796 return (-1);
797
798 match = 1;
799 for (k = 0; match && k < t; k++)
800 {
801 if (tos[j][k] != tos[i][k] || froms[j][k] != froms[i][k])
802 match = 0;
803 }
804
805 if (match)
806 return (j);
807 }
808
809 return (-1);
810}

812static int
813pack_vector(int vector)
814{
815 int i, j, k, l;
816 int t;
817 int loc;
818 int ok;
819 Value_t *from;
820 Value_t *to;
821 int newmax;
822
823 i = order[vector];
824 t = tally[i];
825 assert(t);
826
827 from = froms[i];
828 to = tos[i];
829
830 j = lowzero - from[0];
831 for (k = 1; k < t; ++k)
832 if (lowzero - from[k] > j)
833 j = lowzero - from[k];
834 for (;; ++j)
835 {
836 if (j == 0)
837 continue;
838 ok = 1;
839 for (k = 0; ok && k < t; k++)
840 {
841 loc = j + from[k];
842 if (loc >= maxtable - 1)
843 {
844 if (loc >= MAXTABLE - 1)
845 fatal("maximum table size exceeded");
846
847 newmax = maxtable;
848 do
849 {
850 newmax += 200;
851 }
852 while (newmax <= loc);
853
854 table = TREALLOC(Value_t, table, newmax);
855 NO_SPACE(table);
856
857 check = TREALLOC(Value_t, check, newmax);
858 NO_SPACE(check);
859
860 for (l = maxtable; l < newmax; ++l)
861 {
862 table[l] = 0;
863 check[l] = -1;
864 }
865 maxtable = newmax;
866 }
867
868 if (check[loc] != -1)
869 ok = 0;
870 }
871 for (k = 0; ok && k < vector; k++)
872 {
873 if (pos[k] == j)
874 ok = 0;
875 }
876 if (ok)
877 {
878 for (k = 0; k < t; k++)
879 {
880 loc = j + from[k];
881 table[loc] = to[k];
882 check[loc] = from[k];
883 if (loc > high)
884 high = loc;
885 }
886
887 while (check[lowzero] != -1)
888 ++lowzero;
889
890 return (j);
891 }
892 }
893}

895static void
896pack_table(void)
897{
898 int i;
899 Value_t place;
900 int state;
901
902 base = NEW2(nvectors, Value_t);
903 pos = NEW2(nentries, Value_t);
904
905 maxtable = 1000;
906 table = NEW2(maxtable, Value_t);
907 check = NEW2(maxtable, Value_t);
908
909 lowzero = 0;
910 high = 0;
911
912 for (i = 0; i < maxtable; i++)
913 check[i] = -1;
914
915 for (i = 0; i < nentries; i++)
916 {
917 state = matching_vector(i);
918
919 if (state < 0)
920 place = (Value_t)pack_vector(i);
921 else
922 place = base[state];
923
924 pos[i] = place;
925 base[order[i]] = place;
926 }
927
928 for (i = 0; i < nvectors; i++)
929 {
930 if (froms[i])
931 FREE(froms[i]);
932 if (tos[i])
933 FREE(tos[i]);
934 }
935
936 DO_FREE(froms);
937 DO_FREE(tos);
938 DO_FREE(tally);
939 DO_FREE(width);
940 DO_FREE(pos);
941}

1159static int
1160is_C_identifier(char *name)
1161{
1162 char *s;
1163 int c;
1164
1165 s = name;
1166 c = *s;
1167 if (c == '"')
1168 {
1169 c = *++s;
1170 if (!IS_NAME1(c))
1171 return (0);
1172 while ((c = *++s) != '"')
1173 {
1174 if (!IS_NAME2(c))
1175 return (0);
1176 }
1177 return (1);
1178 }
1179
1180 if (!IS_NAME1(c))
1181 return (0);
1182 while ((c = *++s) != 0)
1183 {
1184 if (!IS_NAME2(c))
1185 return (0);
1186 }
1187 return (1);

1306static void
1307output_debug(void)
1308{
1309 int i, j, k, max, maxtok;
1310 const char **symnam;
1311 const char *s;
1312
1313 ++outline;
1314 fprintf(code_file, "#define YYFINAL %d\n", final_state);
1315
1316 outline += output_yydebug(code_file);
1317
1318 if (rflag)
1319 {
1320 output_yydebug(output_file);
1321 }
1322
1323 maxtok = 0;
1324 for (i = 0; i < ntokens; ++i)
1325 if (symbol_value[i] > maxtok)
1326 maxtok = symbol_value[i];
1327
1328 /* symbol_value[$accept] = -1 */
1329 /* symbol_value[<goal>] = 0 */
1330 /* remaining non-terminals start at 1 */
1331 max = maxtok;
1332 for (i = ntokens; i < nsyms; ++i)
1333 if (((maxtok + 1) + (symbol_value[i] + 1)) > max)
1334 max = (maxtok + 1) + (symbol_value[i] + 1);
1335
1336 ++outline;
1337 fprintf(code_file, "#define YYMAXTOKEN %d\n", maxtok);
1338
1339 ++outline;
1340 fprintf(code_file, "#define YYUNDFTOKEN %d\n", max + 1);
1341
1342 ++outline;
1343 fprintf(code_file, "#define YYTRANSLATE(a) ((a) > YYMAXTOKEN ? "
1344 "YYUNDFTOKEN : (a))\n");
1345
1346 symnam = TMALLOC(const char *, max + 2);
1347 NO_SPACE(symnam);
1348
1349 /* Note that it is not necessary to initialize the element */
1350 /* symnam[max]. */
1351#if defined(YYBTYACC)
1352 for (i = 0; i < max; ++i)
1353 symnam[i] = 0;
1354 for (i = nsyms - 1; i >= 0; --i)
1355 symnam[symbol_pval[i]] = symbol_name[i];
1356 symnam[max + 1] = "illegal-symbol";
1357#else
1358 for (i = 0; i <= max; ++i)
1359 symnam[i] = 0;
1360 for (i = ntokens - 1; i >= 2; --i)
1361 symnam[symbol_value[i]] = symbol_name[i];
1362 symnam[0] = "end-of-file";
1363 symnam[max + 1] = "illegal-symbol";
1364#endif
1365
1366 /*
1367 * bison's yytname[] array is roughly the same as byacc's yyname[] array.
1368 * The difference is that byacc does not predefine "$undefined".
1369 *
1370 * If the grammar declares "%token-table", define symbol "yytname" so
1371 * an application such as ntpd can build.
1372 */
1373 if (token_table)
1374 {
1375 if (!rflag)
1376 {
1377 output_line("#undef yytname");
1378 output_line("#define yytname yyname");
1379 }
1380 }
1381 else
1382 {
1383 output_line("#if YYDEBUG");
1384 }
1385
1386 start_str_table("name");
1387 j = 80;
1388 for (i = 0; i <= max + 1; ++i)
1389 {
1390 if ((s = symnam[i]) != 0)
1391 {
1392 if (s[0] == '"')
1393 {
1394 k = 7;
1395 while (*++s != '"')
1396 {
1397 ++k;
1398 if (*s == '\\')
1399 {
1400 k += 2;
1401 if (*++s == '\\')
1402 ++k;
1403 }
1404 }
1405 j += k;
1406 if (j > 80)
1407 {
1408 output_newline();
1409 j = k;
1410 }
1411 fprintf(output_file, "\"\\\"");
1412 s = symnam[i];
1413 while (*++s != '"')
1414 {
1415 if (*s == '\\')
1416 {
1417 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\");
1418 if (*++s == '\\')
1419 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\");
1420 else
1421 putc(*s, output_file);
1422 }
1423 else
1424 putc(*s, output_file);
1425 }
1426 fprintf(output_file, "\\\"\",");
1427 }
1428 else if (s[0] == '\'')
1429 {
1430 if (s[1] == '"')
1431 {
1432 j += 7;
1433 if (j > 80)
1434 {
1435 output_newline();
1436 j = 7;
1437 }
1438 fprintf(output_file, "\"'\\\"'\",");
1439 }
1440 else
1441 {
1442 k = 5;
1443 while (*++s != '\'')
1444 {
1445 ++k;
1446 if (*s == '\\')
1447 {
1448 k += 2;
1449 if (*++s == '\\')
1450 ++k;
1451 }
1452 }
1453 j += k;
1454 if (j > 80)
1455 {
1456 output_newline();
1457 j = k;
1458 }
1459 fprintf(output_file, "\"'");
1460 s = symnam[i];
1461 while (*++s != '\'')
1462 {
1463 if (*s == '\\')
1464 {
1465 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\");
1466 if (*++s == '\\')
1467 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\");
1468 else
1469 putc(*s, output_file);
1470 }
1471 else
1472 putc(*s, output_file);
1473 }
1474 fprintf(output_file, "'\",");
1475 }
1476 }
1477 else
1478 {
1479 k = (int)strlen(s) + 3;
1480 j += k;
1481 if (j > 80)
1482 {
1483 output_newline();
1484 j = k;
1485 }
1486 putc('"', output_file);
1487 do
1488 {
1489 putc(*s, output_file);
1490 }
1491 while (*++s);
1492 fprintf(output_file, "\",");
1493 }
1494 }
1495 else
1496 {
1497 j += 2;
1498 if (j > 80)
1499 {
1500 output_newline();
1501 j = 2;
1502 }
1503 fprintf(output_file, "0,");
1504 }
1505 }
1506 end_table();
1507 FREE(symnam);
1508
1509 if (token_table)
1510 output_line("#if YYDEBUG");
1511 start_str_table("rule");
1512 for (i = 2; i < nrules; ++i)
1513 {
1514 fprintf(output_file, "\"%s :", symbol_name[rlhs[i]]);
1515 for (j = rrhs[i]; ritem[j] > 0; ++j)
1516 {
1517 s = symbol_name[ritem[j]];
1518 if (s[0] == '"')
1519 {
1520 fprintf(output_file, " \\\"");
1521 while (*++s != '"')
1522 {
1523 if (*s == '\\')
1524 {
1525 if (s[1] == '\\')
1526 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\\\\\");
1527 else
1528 fprintf(output_file, "\\\\%c", s[1]);
1529 ++s;
1530 }
1531 else
1532 putc(*s, output_file);
1533 }
1534 fprintf(output_file, "\\\"");
1535 }
1536 else if (s[0] == '\'')
1537 {
1538 if (s[1] == '"')
1539 fprintf(output_file, " '\\\"'");
1540 else if (s[1] == '\\')
1541 {
1542 if (s[2] == '\\')
1543 fprintf(output_file, " '\\\\\\\\");
1544 else
1545 fprintf(output_file, " '\\\\%c", s[2]);
1546 s += 2;
1547 while (*++s != '\'')
1548 putc(*s, output_file);
1549 putc('\'', output_file);
1550 }
1551 else
1552 fprintf(output_file, " '%c'", s[1]);
1553 }
1554 else
1555 fprintf(output_file, " %s", s);
1556 }
1557 fprintf(output_file, "\",");
1558 output_newline();
1559 }
1560
1561 end_table();
1562 output_line("#endif");
1563}

1743 else

1752 putl_code(fp, "#else\n");
1753 if (pure_parser && lex_param)
1754 {
1755#if defined(YYBTYACC)

1759 else

1762 puts_param_types(fp, lex_param, 0);
1763 putl_code(fp, ")\n");
1764
1765#if defined(YYBTYACC)

1768 else

1771 puts_param_names(fp, lex_param, 0);

1774 else if (pure_parser)

1781 putl_code(fp, "# define YYLEX yylex(&yylval, &yylloc)\n");
1782 }
1783 else
1784#endif
1785 {
1786 putl_code(fp, "# define YYLEX_DECL() yylex(YYSTYPE *yylval)\n");
1787 putl_code(fp, "# define YYLEX yylex(&yylval)\n");
1788 }
1789 }
1790 else if (lex_param)
1791 {
1792 puts_code(fp, "# define YYLEX_DECL() yylex(");
1793 puts_param_types(fp, lex_param, 0);
1794 putl_code(fp, ")\n");
1795

1797 puts_param_names(fp, lex_param, 0);
1798 putl_code(fp, ")\n");
1799 }
1800 else
1801 {
1802 putl_code(fp, "# define YYLEX_DECL() yylex(void)\n");
1803 putl_code(fp, "# define YYLEX yylex()\n");
1804 }
1805 putl_code(fp, "#endif\n");
1806
1807 /*
1808 * Provide a prototype for yylex for the simplest case. This is done for
1809 * better compatibility with older yacc's, but can be a problem if someone
1810 * uses "static int yylex(void);"
1811 */
1812 if (!pure_parser
1813#if defined(YYBTYACC)
1814 && !backtrack
1815#endif
1816 && !strcmp(symbol_prefix, "yy"))
1817 {
1818 putl_code(fp, "\n");
1819 putl_code(fp, "#if !(defined(yylex) || defined(YYSTATE))\n");
1820 putl_code(fp, "int YYLEX_DECL();\n");
1821 putl_code(fp, "#endif\n");
1822 }
1823}

1905static void
1906output_yydestruct_impl(void)
1907{
1908 int i;
1909 char *s, *destructor_code;
1910
1911 putc_code(code_file, '\n');
1912 putl_code(code_file, "/* Release memory associated with symbol. */\n");
1913 putl_code(code_file, "#if ! defined YYDESTRUCT_IS_DECLARED\n");
1914 putl_code(code_file, "static void\n");
1915 putl_code(code_file, "YYDESTRUCT_DECL()\n");
1916 putl_code(code_file, "{\n");
1917 putl_code(code_file, " switch (psymb)\n");
1918 putl_code(code_file, " {\n");
1919 for (i = 2; i < nsyms; ++i)
1920 {
1921 if ((destructor_code = symbol_destructor[i]) != NULL)
1922 {
1923 ++outline;
1924 fprintf(code_file, "\tcase %d:\n", symbol_pval[i]);
1925 /* comprehend the number of lines in the destructor code */
1926 for (s = destructor_code; (s = strchr(s, '\n')) != NULL; s++)
1927 ++outline;
1928 puts_code(code_file, destructor_code);
1929 putc_code(code_file, '\n');
1930 putl_code(code_file, "\tbreak;\n");
1931 write_code_lineno(code_file);
1932 FREE(destructor_code);
1933 }
1934 }
1935 putl_code(code_file, " }\n");
1936 putl_code(code_file, "}\n");
1937 putl_code(code_file, "#define YYDESTRUCT_IS_DECLARED 1\n");
1938 putl_code(code_file, "#endif\n");

1983static void
1984output_externs(FILE * fp, const char *const section[])
1985{
1986 int i;
1987 const char *s;
1988
1989 for (i = 0; (s = section[i]) != 0; ++i)
1990 {
1991 /* prefix non-blank lines that don't start with
1992 C pre-processor directives with 'extern ' */
1993 if (*s && (*s != '#'))
1994 fputs("extern\t", fp);
1995 if (fp == code_file)
1996 ++outline;
1997 fprintf(fp, "%s\n", s);
1998 }

2001void
2002output(void)
2003{
2004 FILE *fp;
2005
2006 free_itemsets();
2007 free_shifts();
2008 free_reductions();
2009
2010#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2011 output_backtracking_parser(output_file);
2012 if (rflag)
2013 output_backtracking_parser(code_file);
2014#endif
2015
2016 if (iflag)
2017 {
2018 write_code_lineno(code_file);
2019 ++outline;
2020 fprintf(code_file, "#include \"%s\"\n", externs_file_name);
2021 fp = externs_file;
2022 }
2023 else
2024 fp = code_file;
2025
2026 output_prefix(fp);
2027 output_pure_parser(fp);
2028#if defined(YY_NO_LEAKS)
2029 output_no_leaks(fp);
2030#endif
2031 output_stored_text(fp);
2032 output_stype(fp);
2033#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2034 if (locations)
2035 output_ltype(fp);
2036#endif
2037 output_parse_decl(fp);
2038 output_lex_decl(fp);
2039 output_error_decl(fp);
2040#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2041 if (destructor)
2042 output_yydestruct_decl(fp);
2043#endif
2044 if (iflag || !rflag)
2045 {
2046 write_section(fp, xdecls);
2047 }
2048
2049 if (iflag)
2050 {
2051 fprintf(externs_file, "\n");
2052 output_yydebug(externs_file);
2053 output_externs(externs_file, global_vars);
2054 if (!pure_parser)
2055 output_externs(externs_file, impure_vars);
2056 }
2057
2058 if (iflag)
2059 {
2060 if (dflag)
2061 {
2062 ++outline;
2063 fprintf(code_file, "#include \"%s\"\n", defines_file_name);
2064 }
2065 else
2066 output_defines(externs_file);
2067 }
2068 else
2069 {
2070 putc_code(code_file, '\n');
2071 output_defines(code_file);
2072 }
2073
2074 if (dflag)
2075 {
2076 start_defines_file();
2077 output_defines(defines_file);
2078 end_defines_file();
2079 }
2080
2081 output_rule_data();
2082 output_yydefred();
2083#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2084 output_accessing_symbols();
2085#endif
2086 output_actions();
2087 free_parser();
2088 output_debug();
2089 if (rflag)
2090 {
2091 write_section(code_file, xdecls);
2092 output_YYINT_typedef(code_file);
2093 write_section(code_file, tables);
2094 }
2095 write_section(code_file, global_vars);
2096 if (!pure_parser)
2097 {
2098 write_section(code_file, impure_vars);
2099 }
2100 write_section(code_file, hdr_defs);
2101 if (!pure_parser)
2102 {
2103 write_section(code_file, hdr_vars);
2104 }
2105 output_trailing_text();
2106#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2107 if (destructor)
2108 output_yydestruct_impl();
2109#endif
2110 write_section(code_file, body_1);
2111 if (pure_parser)
2112 {
2113 write_section(code_file, body_vars);
2114 }
2115 write_section(code_file, body_2);
2116 if (pure_parser)
2117 {
2118 write_section(code_file, init_vars);
2119 }
2120#if defined(YYBTYACC)
2121 if (initial_action)
2122 output_initial_action();
2123#endif
2124 write_section(code_file, body_3);
2125 output_semantic_actions();
2126 write_section(code_file, trailer);
2127}
